parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and structural failure of the frame can lead to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the frame
rusting of the undercarriage
corrosion of the leaf spring mounts
and failure of the suspension components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration and shimmying of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: Vibration or shimmying of the vehicle
uneven tire wear
and loose or worn-out suspension components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of electrical systems can lead to loss of critical vehicle functions, such as brake lights, turn signals, and door locks, which can increase the risk of accidents and compromise safety.
symptoms: Rear turn signal lights
brake lamps
and headlamps experience permanent loss
cruise control stops functioning
power door locks
power windows
and power rearview mirrors stop working
and remote key entry malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the climate control fan can cause discomfort and distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Climate control fan only works in position 4
resistor on circuit board fails
and connector to motor is burnt and slightly melted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the anti-theft Passlock system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential emergency situations.
symptoms: Vehicle won't start due to anti-theft Passlock system
Passlock light is on
and requires a 10-minute wait to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents and safety risks.
symptoms: Ignition switch recall notice received
but dealership refused to repair due to mileage limitations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of door locks and windows can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential security breaches.
symptoms: Brake lights
door locks
and windows malfunction
and rearview mirrors stop working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Severe rust and corrosion of the frame can cause structural failure, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal rattling noise
spare tire/wheel falls from under the vehicle
holes in the frame
frame disintegrating
bent frame
and rusted-through sections of the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Key Hole on Passenger Side Door
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of a key hole on the passenger side door can pose a safety risk, especially when parents need to unlock the door to let their children out, potentially exposing them to oncoming traffic.
symptoms: No key hole on passenger side door
difficulty unlocking door from passenger side
and increased risk of injury or accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken tailgate straps can cause the tailgate to fall open, potentially leading to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Broken tailgate straps
tailgate falls open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of skid plates can increase the risk of damage to the vehicle's underside, potentially leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: Skid plates not installed
despite being listed as standard equipment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle position sensor fault can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to reduced acceleration and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The reduced power light comes on the dashboard
the vehicle has no power
the throttle position sensor fault is detected on the scope.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cylinder head leaking air can cause the engine to misfire, idle poorly, and waste fuel, leading to reduced vehicle performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle dies at stop signs
is in a constant misfire state while driving
has poor gas mileage
and leaks air from the cylinder head.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle erupts into flames
the fire originates from under the glove compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exhaust manifold failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to reduced acceleration and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The exhaust manifold breaks and falls off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent starting issues can cause inconvenience and potentially strand the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start at intermittent times
the starter and alternator are checked and found to be fine
the fuel pump has been replaced but the problem persists.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine intake valve seat wear can cause the engine to misfire and idle poorly, leading to reduced vehicle performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine intake valve seats are subject to abnormal wear
possibly resulting in misfiring and rough engine idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The air conditioning whine can cause annoyance and discomfort to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: A high-pitched whining noise comes from the engine when the air conditioning is used
the noise is not constant and sounds like it occurs when the air conditioning compressor kicks in.
